  "text": "k being a two-dimensional Bloch vector, and G denoting a two-dimensional reciprocal lattice vector. Those of the material parameters which are periodic functions can be Fourier-expanded. For Z modes, described by [CITATION_1] , Fourier expansion can be applied to the inverse of mass density, , ρ −1 and to the coefficient ; μ in the case of XY modes also the coefficient λ can be Fourier-expanded:",
